cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel multi-hop ride-sharing algorithm that uses deep reinforcement learning to learn optimal vehicle dispatch and matching decisions. This falls under the domain of AI and machine learning. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep reinforcement learning to train the proposed algorithm, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for multi-hop ride-sharing, which involves multiple agents (i.e., vehicles and customers) interacting with each other. This falls under the domain of multi-agent systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an algorithm for optimizing the dispatch and matching decisions of ride-sharing vehicles, which can be seen as a control problem. This falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for multi-hop ride-sharing, which involves multiple vehicles and customers. This falls under the domain of distributed computing.
